# .dockerignore — HotLink Cache
# Excludes files from the Docker build context sent to Railway.
# Keep this list TIGHT — incorrect exclusions cause "not found" COPY errors.

# ── Build outputs (regenerated inside Docker) ─────────────────────────────────
**/.next
**/dist
**/.turbo
**/build

# ── Secrets (must NEVER be in the image) ─────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.key
solana-dev.json

# ── Move / Aptos compiled artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────
contracts/move/build

# ── Dev/test scripts (not needed in production image) ────────────────────────
scripts/
extensions/

# ── Docs (save build-context bytes) ──────────────────────────────────────────
DEPLOYMENT.md
TESTING-SCENARIOS.md

# ── OS / Editor ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode
.idea

# ── Git ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git
.gitignore

# ── Logs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log

# NOTE: node_modules is intentionally NOT excluded globally.
# The deps stage copies manifests only (no node_modules from host).
# The builder stage uses COPY . . but node_modules won't exist on Railway's
# build worker (they run a fresh clone). On local Docker builds, add:
#   **/node_modules
# to this file if you have local node_modules that would pollute the context.
